title: Quarterly Financial Report — Q2 2026
summary: Al-Rayyan Commercial Bank Q.P.S.C. · Consolidated unaudited results for the three months ended 2026-06-30
meta: | type: financial-report | ref: REP-2026-Q2-017 | period: Q2 2026 | prepared-by: Group Finance | prepared-for: Board Audit Committee | basis: IFRS · unaudited | theme: corporate | date: 2026-07-22

toc:

section: 1. Executive Summary
text: Al-Rayyan Commercial Bank delivered a resilient performance in the second quarter of 2026, with net income rising on the back of expanding net interest margin, disciplined cost control, and a lower cost of risk. Total assets crossed the QAR 1.2 trillion mark for the first time, driven by selective loan growth in the corporate and SME segments and continued deposit mobilisation.
text: The Group maintained capital and liquidity ratios comfortably above regulatory minima, and the Board has approved the interim results for release to the regulator and the market.

info: All figures are presented in Qatari Riyals (QAR) on a consolidated basis under IFRS and are unaudited unless otherwise stated. | type: info

section: 2. Key Performance Indicators
text: The headline indicators below compare Q2 2026 against the prior quarter and the internal Board-approved targets for the period.

metric: Net Income | value: 4120 | unit: QAR millions | trend: up | target: 3850 | period: Q2 2026
metric: Return on Equity (ROE) | value: 18.6 | unit: % | trend: up | target: 17.5 | period: Q2 2026
metric: Return on Assets (ROA) | value: 1.38 | unit: % | trend: flat | period: Q2 2026
metric: Net Interest Margin (NIM) | value: 2.94 | unit: % | trend: up | period: Q2 2026
metric: Cost-to-Income Ratio | value: 24.1 | unit: % | trend: down | target: 26.0 | period: Q2 2026
metric: Earnings Per Share (EPS) | value: 0.34 | unit: QAR | trend: up | period: Q2 2026

text: Net income of QAR 4,120 million exceeded the Board target of QAR 3,850 million by *7.0%*, supported by an 11 basis-point expansion in net interest margin and a one-third reduction in the quarterly cost of risk.

break:

