section: 5. Capital & Liquidity
text: The Group's regulatory ratios, computed under the Qatar Central Bank Basel III framework, remained well above the prescribed minima throughout the quarter.

metric: Common Equity Tier 1 (CET1) | value: 15.8 | unit: % | target: 8.5 | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: Total Capital Adequacy Ratio | value: 19.2 | unit: % | target: 12.5 | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: Liquidity Coverage Ratio (LCR) | value: 138 | unit: % | target: 100 | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: Net Stable Funding Ratio (NSFR) | value: 119 | unit: % | target: 100 | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: Leverage Ratio | value: 9.4 | unit: % | target: 3.0 | period: 30 Jun 2026

info: All capital and liquidity ratios were in full compliance with Qatar Central Bank requirements at the reporting date. | type: success

section: 6. Asset Quality
text: Asset quality continued to improve as legacy exposures were resolved and new originations were concentrated in higher-rated obligors.

metric: Non-Performing Loan (NPL) Ratio | value: 1.9 | unit: % | trend: down | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: NPL Coverage Ratio | value: 104 | unit: % | trend: up | period: 30 Jun 2026
metric: Cost of Risk | value: 0.41 | unit: % | trend: down | period: Q2 2026

risk: Concentration in real-estate sector exposure | severity: medium | mitigation: cap at 22% of gross loans; quarterly stress testing | owner: Chief Risk Officer
risk: Rising funding cost from policy-rate environment | severity: medium | mitigation: lengthen deposit tenor; grow current/savings account mix | owner: Group Treasurer
risk: Single-name large-borrower default | severity: low | mitigation: single-obligor limit at 15% of capital base | owner: Chief Credit Officer

break:

