metric: Largest Contributor | value: Corporate Banking | period: Q2 2026

section: 8. Outlook
text: Management expects continued single-digit balance-sheet growth in the second half of 2026, with net interest margin stabilising as funding costs normalise. The full-year cost-to-income ratio is expected to remain below the 26% target.

guidance: Full-year net income growth | range: 6% to 9% | basis: constant currency | period: FY 2026
guidance: Loan book growth | range: 5% to 7% | period: H2 2026
guidance: Dividend payout | range: 45% to 50% of net profit | period: FY 2026

info: This outlook contains forward-looking statements that are subject to market and macroeconomic conditions and should not be read as a guarantee of future performance. | type: warning

section: 9. Approvals
text: The interim consolidated results for Q2 2026 were reviewed and approved by the following officers prior to release. This document is presented pre-seal; the cryptographic seal and signatures are applied on issuance.

approve: Financial statements prepared in accordance with IFRS | by: Mariam Al-Suwaidi | role: Group Chief Financial Officer | at: 2026-07-20
approve: Risk and asset-quality disclosures reviewed | by: Khalid Al-Mansoori | role: Chief Risk Officer | at: 2026-07-20
approve: Results reviewed by the Audit Committee | by: Dr. Hessa Al-Jaber | role: Chair, Board Audit Committee | at: 2026-07-21
approve: Approved for release to the regulator and market | by: Abdulaziz Al-Rayyan | role: Group Chief Executive Officer | at: 2026-07-22

signline: Group Chief Executive Officer
signline: Chair, Board Audit Committee

section: 10. Notes & Definitions
def: Net Interest Margin (NIM) | meaning: Net interest income as a percentage of average interest-earning assets, annualised.
def: Cost of Risk | meaning: Annualised net impairment charge as a percentage of average gross loans and advances.
def: CET1 | meaning: Common Equity Tier 1 capital as a percentage of risk-weighted assets under the Basel III framework.
def: Non-Performing Loan (NPL) | meaning: A loan classified as Stage 3 under IFRS 9 or more than 90 days past due.

cite: Qatar Central Bank — Basel III Capital Adequacy Framework | section: Pillar 1
cite: IFRS 9 Financial Instruments | section: Expected Credit Losses

text: Comparative figures for Q1 2026 are unaudited. Percentages are calculated on unrounded figures and may not recompute exactly from the rounded amounts presented. | end: REP-2026-Q2-017
